The best thing about all of the Despicable Me movies is all the visual comedy, schtick. You can watch the same movie several times and still not get all of the little gems of rib ticklers. All of the other movies in this series followed the plot line, having a good climactic encounter with the good and bad guys and a happy conclusion.<br /><br />None of the key elements of a great movie are in this one. The story line gets fuzzy about halfway through. The plot weakens. The ending is actually anti-climatic.<br /><br />All of the humor is there. Even enough double entendre for us grownups. Plenty of visual gags. However, this is the first of the series that in my opinion 'bombed' and will not watch it again. It was that dissappointing.
